   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Default stack size differs across operating systems. E.g. the defaults for thread stack sizes: Linux: 8MiB, Windows 1MiB, FreeBSD 2MiB, OpenBSD 512 KiB.\r\n\r\nIt would be sensible to lower the stack size used in all CI jobs to the lowest default, so we don't miss stack overflow bugs that only occur with small stack sizes.",
